{
  "texts": [
    "The performance measurements include the top-1 accuracy of context matching, mean squared error (MSE) of pose prediction, inception score (IS) of generated videos and top-1 accuracy of downstream action recognition.",
    "The results in Table II show a consistent improvement in action recognition accuracy as the performance of the pretext tasks increases, which indicates the strong correlations between various pretext and downstream tasks.TABLE III: Comparison of feature f d from different layers of G p encoder.",
    "Layer UCF101 HMDB51 Layer 2 72.0 36.9 Layer 4 74.5 37.2 Layer 6 75.1 38.4TABLE IV: Comparison of feature f s with different loss functions.",
    "Objective UCF101 HMDB51 L2 Loss 70.2 33.4 InfoNCE 72.5 40.2 MI-InfoNCE 73.1 40.2Selection of Dynamic Motion Feature.",
    "In order to locate the hidden layer which enriches the most dynamic information, we pretrain the pose generator G p on poses from UCF101 dataset and use features from different layers of encoder in G p as dynamic motion features f d. We report the results of different f d finetuned on action recognition task."
  ]
